de.ur.iw.navigame.sessions

Class SessionCreation

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ur.iw.navigame.sessions.SessionCreation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServletRequestHandler

    public class SessionCreation
extends java.lang.Object
implements ServletRequestHandler
    The SessionCreation initiates a new session of the game by creating a unique ID and selecting two rooms, one of which will be the start and the other one of which will be the goal of the path.

      • getRandomRoomId

        private org.json.JSONObject getRandomRoomId(java.lang.String areaName,
                                  org.json.JSONObject areaFile)
        Selects a random (valid) room from the file, builds a JSONObject containing its data and returns that. valid means that the room has to have a roomid.
        Parameters:
        areaName - name of an area (e.g. "PT")
        areaFile - the long files containing a graph and a list of all the rooms in an area
        Returns:
        a {roomid: string, area: string, level: int}-type JSON object
